race.comment: HELLISH (2) turned at the tail of the field and couldn't get involved last Saturday in a 1000m BM78 of metro standing. Has won four from ten at today's journey and this is a far weaker race. It all sets up perfectly for a return to form. SMART SERENADE (9) was 33 days between runs when a tiring third over 1300m at Hawkesbury last time out. More effective at 1400m than 1200m but with a soft run out of gate one he should be competitive. CONFESS OUR DREAMS (1) was not sighted in four Saturday metro races before a better effort last start, beaten 2.5 lengths over 1100m at Canterbury. Back further in grade now and might have found her level. No surprise to see something positive here. MAH ALI (16) is better placed today after failing in a BM74 over the mile at Queanbeyan recently. Best form from earlier this prep reads well so keep her safe. HOUSE OF CARDS (3) is a strong fresh performer back from an 11-week break. Has been in work for a while so should be forward enough to run well.
